column3:
<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Quroll Ja is eager to teach you about blessed siblings.
You're part of the Third Promise's retinue, aren't you? I was glad to hear you express an interest in our ways.
Perhaps you'd be interested in learning more about our culture? I could teach you, if you'd like.
The statue behind me holds great cultural significance to our people. Feel free to ask about anything that catches your interest.
The statue behind me represents much and more about Mamook. Take a look from over there and I'll explain whatever you're curious about.

Study the statue of blessed siblings. You may move the camera, as well as zoom in and out. Target a section and learn more details with <If(Equal(PlayerParameter(80),0))><UIForeground>F20222</UIForeground><UIForeground>01</UIForeground><Else/><CommandIcon(15)/> / <CommandIcon(8)/></If>.
In conclusion, this statue symbolizes the heart of Mamook, down to the stone it was carved from─the very stone left by the Yok Huy who ruled these lands long ago.
Our predecessors reimagined the structures abandoned here and built the city you see today, creating a future all their own.
...Unlike their descendants, now shackled to a past, land, and practice that have poisoned Mamook's prospects. I wonder if we are truly capable of change.
But no─as our ancestors found their way, so will we. As we seek to discover what we might yet become, I pray you never forget all that Mamook once was.
